    "summary": "Since 2007, Vincent van der Heijde is Senior Project Manager in Group Risk Management (GRM) at Atradius, involved in activities related to the Group Pricing Model, the Economic Capital Model (SCR model), the implementation of Solvency II, Risk Governance and other Risk Management activities. Before his move to GRM, Vincent worked as a buyer underwriter for over 6 years and has taken part in several side activities. He is an internal staff trainer and represents GRM in several committees. Vincent was member of the Dutch and European Works Council. From 2005 until 2010 Vincent was the employee representative in negotiating the Collective Labour Agreement. \nSince 2017 Vincent uses his skills to maintain and improve Business Continuity within the group, working together with the Group BCM Manager. Vincent participated in several internal and external trainings: Underwriting related training, Financial Statement Analyses, career self-management (4 weeks at Schouten en Nelissen), Stepping Forward (4 weeks Management Development program at Atradius), Project Management (MCE, Brussels), Risk Management in projects (MCE, Geneva), Prince 2 initiator and practitioner. \n\ndrs. Vincent van der Heijde has a MA in Public Administration (Erasmus University Rotterdam, specialisation: Safety and security management, 1996) and a Post-graduation in risk and crises management (DESS, University of Paris1, Pantheon-Sorbonne, 1996).\nVincent finished his studies by doing a research project at the Fire Brigade of Rotterdam, department of public safety. After his studies Vincent worked twice for the Firebrigade of Rotterdam, department of operational preparation. Vincent speaks four European languages fluent (Dutch, English, Portuguese, French) and some Spanish & German.\n\nSpecialties: Communication, project management, trainer, among others.",
